<p>Harry Deutsch, emeritus professor of philosophy at Illinois State University, has died.<span id="more-54781"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-54782 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/deutsch-harry.jpg" alt="" width="357" height="500" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/deutsch-harry.jpg 357w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/deutsch-harry-214x300.jpg 214w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 357px) 100vw, 357px" /></p>
<p>Professor Deutsch was known for his work in philosophical logic and philosophy of language. You can learn more about his work <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/harry-deutsch" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and <a href="https://independent.academia.edu/DeutschHarry" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>Professor Deutsch spent most of his career at Illinois State. Before that, he held appointments at Indiana University Bloomington and the University of California, Los Angeles, among other places. His earned his PhD from UCLA.</p>
<p>A brief obituary is <a href="https://www.legacy.com/us/obituaries/pantagraph/name/harry-deutsch-obituary?id=59231813" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>. In a comments on it, Nathan Salmon (UCSB) calls Professor Deutsch &#8220;the single most under-rated figure in analytic philosophy.&#8221;</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/08/27/harry-deutsch-1942-2025/">Harry Deutsch (1942-2025)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>